    "shortDesc": "Major depressive disorder, recurrent, moderate",
    "longDesc": "Major depressive disorder, recurrent, moderate",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means a person has experienced depression multiple times throughout their life, and they're currently in a moderate episode. Moderate depression is more serious than mild sadness—it typically involves persistent low mood, loss of interest in activities, sleep changes, and difficulty concentrating that interferes noticeably with daily work or relationships, but the person can usually still function with effort.",
