    "shortDesc": "Generalized anxiety disorder",
    "longDesc": "Generalized anxiety disorder",
    "plainEnglish": "Generalized anxiety disorder (GAD) is a mental health condition where a person feels persistent, excessive worry about everyday situations—like work, finances, health, or family—that lasts for at least six months. Unlike normal stress or occasional worry, this anxiety is hard to control, interferes with daily life, and is often accompanied by physical symptoms like restlessness, fatigue, difficulty concentrating, muscle tension, or sleep problems.",
