    "shortDesc": "Anxiety disorder, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Anxiety disorder, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "An anxiety disorder is a mental health condition where a person experiences persistent, excessive worry or fear that interferes with daily life. This could involve physical symptoms like racing heartbeat, sweating, or trouble sleeping, and emotional symptoms like constant nervousness or panic. When doctors use 'unspecified,' it means they've diagnosed anxiety but haven't determined the exact type (like generalized anxiety, panic disorder, or social anxiety).",
