    "shortDesc": "Attn-defct hyperactivity disorder, predom inattentive type",
    "longDesc": "Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder, predominantly inattentive type",
    "plainEnglish": "ADHD, inattentive type is a condition where a person struggles mainly with paying attention, organizing tasks, and following through on activities, rather than with hyperactivity or impulsiveness. People with this type have difficulty staying focused, remembering instructions, and managing their time, which can make school, work, or daily tasks feel overwhelming. Unlike the more energetic form of ADHD, this type is often quieter and harder to notice, but it causes real challenges in concentration and executive functioning.",
